radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: Computed tomography (CT) angiography of the chest
radiographic_examinations.findings: No evidence of aortic dissection or proximal pulmonary embolism. The aorta appeared normal.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT angiography of the head, neck, abdomen, and pelvis
radiographic_examinations.findings: Vessels in the head and neck were patent with no evidence of aneurysm, dissection, or luminal irregularity. Delayed-phase images showed multiple small, bilateral, wedge-shaped cortical defects consistent with remote renal infarctions.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Subtle luminal irregularities in renal arteries consistent with previous renal-artery dissections were noted, but no findings suggestive of fibromuscular dysplasia.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Filling defect in the first obtuse marginal branch of the left circumflex coronary artery with sudden, diffuse narrowing of the vessel lumen and an irregular filling pattern, consistent with coronary-artery dissection.
